# Task 25 Evidence: Default Uses Approximate Count

## Test: Default behavior uses approximate (non-cached) count

### Implementation
- src/lib/clickhouse/stream.ts line 120-128: Default is approximate (no caching)
- useExactCount parameter defaults to false

### Verification
1. Default useExactCount is false - VERIFIED (stream.ts line 48: useExactCount = false)
2. When false, uses direct count() query without caching - VERIFIED (stream.ts lines 121-128)
3. No cache hit/miss tracking for approximate - VERIFIED

### Code Evidence
```typescript
// stream.ts - Default behavior
export async function* fetchChunks({
  ...
  useExactCount = false,  // DEFAULT IS APPROXIMATE
}: FetchChunksParams) {
  ...
  // Uses regular count() without caching
  if (useExactCount) {
    // Exact count with caching
  } else {
    // Default: approximate count (no caching)
    countPromise = client
      .query(`SELECT count() as cnt FROM ${tableSource} ${countWhereClause}`)
      .then((res) => Number(res.data[0]?.cnt) || 0);
  }
}
```

### route.ts Evidence
```typescript
// route.ts - Query param parsing
const useExactCount = searchParams.get("exact") === "true";
// Only true when user explicitly requests it
```

### Behavior Summary
| Scenario | Count Type | Cached |
|----------|-----------|--------|
| Default (no param) | Approximate | No |
| exact=false | Approximate | No |
| exact=true | Exact | Yes |

This preserves existing performance for large tables while allowing users to opt-in to exact counts.
